# üéØ Project: Personal Finance Tracker
# Build a complete personal finance tracker that allows users to add expenses, categorize them, save data to files, and generate monthly reports. This final project combines all concepts from Weeks 1-4 into a practical, real-world application.

# üõ†Ô∏è Technical Requirements:
# Implement file operations for data persistence (JSON/CSV)
# Create a modular code structure with separate modules
# Add comprehensive error handling for file operations
# Implement data validation for all inputs
# Generate reports with statistics and visualizations
# Support multiple expense categories
# Add search and filter functionality
# Create a user-friendly menu system
# Implement backup and data recovery features
# üìã Step-by-Step Guide:
# Step 1: Project Architecture
# ‚Ä¢ Create main project folder with subfolders for modules
# ‚Ä¢ Design data structure for expenses
# ‚Ä¢ Plan file formats for data storage
# ‚Ä¢ Create module structure: main.py, expenses.py, file_handler.py, reports.py
# Step 2: Core Data Module
# ‚Ä¢ Create Expense class with attributes (date, amount, category, description)
# ‚Ä¢ Add validation methods for expense data
# ‚Ä¢ Create ExpenseManager class to handle collections of expenses
# ‚Ä¢ Implement methods to add, remove, and search expenses
# Step 3: File Handling Module
# ‚Ä¢ Create functions to save/load expenses to JSON file
# ‚Ä¢ Implement backup functionality
# ‚Ä¢ Add CSV export/import features
# ‚Ä¢ Handle file errors (missing files, permission errors, etc.)
# Step 4: Reports Module
# ‚Ä¢ Create monthly summary reports
# ‚Ä¢ Generate category-wise expense breakdown
# ‚Ä¢ Add expense trend analysis
# ‚Ä¢ Create basic text-based visualizations
# Step 5: Main Application
# ‚Ä¢ Build user-friendly menu system
# ‚Ä¢ Integrate all modules
# ‚Ä¢ Add data validation at user interface level
# ‚Ä¢ Implement search and filter functionality
# Step 6: Advanced Features
# ‚Ä¢ Add budget setting and tracking
# ‚Ä¢ Implement recurring expenses
# ‚Ä¢ Add expense prediction based on history
# ‚Ä¢ Create data export to multiple formats
# Step 7: Testing & Polish
# ‚Ä¢ Test all file operations with edge cases
# ‚Ä¢ Verify data persistence between runs
# ‚Ä¢ Test error handling scenarios
# ‚Ä¢ Add documentation and help system
